<P><STRONG>SimpleLight</STRONG> is sample C code illustrating the use of =
OpenGL.=20
&nbsp; It is intended to accompany the book <EM><STRONG>3D Computer =
Graphics: A=20
mathematical approach with OpenGL</STRONG>, </EM>by Samuel R. Buss, =
Cambridge=20
University Press, 2003. &nbsp; However, it can be used independently as=20
well.</P>
<P><STRONG>SimpleLight </STRONG>illustrates the use Phong lighting in=20
OpenGL.&nbsp; It draws six spheres of different colors, and makes a =
white light=20
revolve around the spheres.&nbsp;&nbsp; It consists of two source files, =

<STRONG>SimpleLight.c</STRONG> and =
<STRONG>SimpleLight.h.</STRONG>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
There are several options available for downloading this program:=20
