<P><STRONG>Things to notice:</STRONG>=20
<OL>
  <LI>Compile and run the program.&nbsp; Try out the keyboard =
controls.&nbsp;=20
  Pressing "r" starts and stops the animation.&nbsp; Pressing "s" =
performs=20
  single steps of the animation.&nbsp;&nbsp; The up and down arrows =
control the=20
  speed of the rotation.&nbsp; Pressing "l" (for local) switches between =
a=20
  positional light and a directional light.=20
  <LI>Note the specular hightlights.=20
  <LI>Note how the diffuse illumination is brightest facing the light, =
and dims=20
  quickly as the surface normals move away from facing the light source. =

  <LI>Note how the bright center of diffuse illumination is not at the =
same=20
  position as the specular hightlight.&nbsp; What is this?=20
  <LI>Note that there is some ambient light (both global ambient light =
and=20
  anbient light from light #0).&nbsp; For this reason, the sides of the =
spheres=20
  facing away the light source are not completely dark.=20
  <LI>Note how the specular highlights change position when the light =
switches=20
  between directional and positional.&nbsp; Note how the diffuse =
lighting=20
  changes when the light switch is made.&nbsp; Explain qualitatively why =
you see=20
  the changes you do.=20
  <LI>The six spheres and the light are all in the same plane (the=20
  xy-plane).&nbsp; Why don't the spheres cast shadows on each other?=20
  <LI>Note how the program used emissive properties to make the light =
glow=20
  white. &nbsp; However the fact that the white sphere is visible is =
independent=20
  of the fact that the light is active and shining. =
</LI></OL></BODY></HTML>
